name: MATH 145
title: Introductory Chaos Theory
description: The Lorenz and Rossler attractors, measures of chaos, attractor reconstruction, and applications from the sciences. Students cannot receive credit for this course and AM 114.

pre_req_data.text: Prerequisite(s): MATH 22 or MATH 23A; MATH 21; MATH 100 or CSE 101. Concurrent enrollment in MATH 145L is required.

class_notes: Sections begin Tuesday, Jan. 16th for Winter 2024.
